"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/ohCBhl7aeGl5j5HIfxG0k.jpg?height=720&width=1280)\\n\\n**Billionaire Ray Dalio, the founder of the world’s largest hedge fund, Bridgewater Associates, has shared his investment strategy with cryptocurrency as part of his portfolio. He warned that cash is the worst investment because it is eaten away by inflation.**\\n\\n## Ray Dalio’s Investment Advice: Cash Is Depreciating, Diversify Portfolio Well\\n\\nBridgewater Associates founder Ray Dalio shared his investment strategy last week. He currently serves as Bridgewater Associates’ chairman and co-chief investment officer. His firm’s clients include endowments, governments, foundations, pensions, and sovereign wealth funds.\\n\\nIn an interview with Yahoo Finance, published Friday, he explained that he views cryptocurrency “as an alternative money in an environment where the value of cash money is depreciating in real terms.” Referring to bitcoin, he opined:\",\"timestamp\":1639985134,\"title\":\"Billionaire Ray Dalio's Investing Advice: Avoid Cash, Think in Inflation-Adjusted Dollars, Crypto Helps Diversify\"},\"digest\":\"V7BhAv_noDhayl0ASAj8HT7AlBy774mokjd7-Q6XGkk\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0x544812e70A62d9d6f465cFBF18FF3dB7e3165b8d\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"xsUsg2BcFfgKMoAVDO4TXCHduUybTPJysBCaCn7Vv6M\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"9G18RlTHCNRQlTSWhPlMZwjDrwLhigzeGH0KM1Om5mE\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"hVySR9Kh4uSLJjFrq5uSv2j2nf5U-2lkzCiOyhxx2ZeVzQy8PpQR8VY_Aut9o0R8Ji3yntXDEqULL_tMtDLZsA\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0x3db155b05f8bdf5f859d3be896a10e58cd1af8dbe5c166c511ac4f46809194c31d292df68c441d4f9ac142976bb4954876dc520c6a3d6c65b6c2fefdad3902261b\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\